OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1781273476
OL,3,CDisgraced surgeon's patient 'failed at
OL,4,Cevery stage' by entire system
OL,6,FAn inquest has heard that a former
OL,7,Fpatient of disgraced surgeon Ian
OL,8,FPaterson was "failed at every
OL,9,Fappointment".
OL,11,FTracey Taylor, a retail manager from
OL,12,FSolihull, died of breast cancer aged
OL,13,Fjust 29 in 1999.
OL,15,FHer inquest is being held as part of
OL,16,Fan investigation by the Coroner to see
OL,17,Fwhether Paterson's treatment
OL,18,Fcontributed towards their deaths in
OL,19,Fany way.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G1/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1781273476
OL,3,CDisgraced surgeon's patient 'failed at
OL,4,Cevery stage' by entire system
OL,6,FPaterson is currently serving a 20-
OL,7,Fyear prison sentence for wounding and
OL,8,Fcarrying out unnecessary operations on
OL,9,Fpatients at hospitals in Birmingham
OL,10,Fand Solihull.
OL,12,FTracey's husband, Norman Taylor, gave
OL,13,Fevidence to the court saying Paterson
OL,14,Fwasn't "the only person to fail
OL,15,FTracey" but that "the fire was already
OL,16,Fburning when he met her, and he let it
OL,17,Fburn."
OL,19,FNorman said Tracey asked Paterson for
OL,20,Fa mastectomy, but he initially said
OL,21,Fshe was "too young".
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1781273476
OL,3,CDisgraced surgeon's patient 'failed at
OL,4,Cevery stage' by entire system
OL,6,FHowever, he later tried to encourage
OL,7,Fher to have cosmetic surgery to even
OL,8,Fup the reconstruction after she had
OL,9,Feventually had a mastectomy, even when
OL,10,Fshe was dying.
OL,12,FNorman told the court, "Why was he
OL,13,F(Paterson) still trying to operate on
OL,14,Fa dying woman? It seems his decisions
OL,15,Fwere to serve more than Tracey."
OL,17,FTracey first went to the GP with a
OL,18,Flump in her right breast in 1997, and
OL,19,FNorman says she had to fight numerous
OL,20,Ftimes to get a referral to the breast
OL,21,Fclinic.
OL,26,@uD@ApmuD@Jpn
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1781273476
OL,3,CDisgraced surgeon's patient 'failed at
OL,4,Cevery stage' by entire system
OL,6,FWhen she did, her lump was
OL,7,Fmisdiagnosed as benign, mainly due,
OL,8,Fthe court heard, to the assumption
OL,9,Fthat her age made it more likely than
OL,10,Fnot that it would be.
OL,12,FFollow-up tests were booked, but the
OL,13,Fcourt heard evidence from Dr Sinha,
OL,14,Fwho treated Tracey only once, that if
OL,15,Fhe had been in charge of her care, he
OL,16,Fwould have redone some of the tests
OL,17,Fand had Tracey in for an appointment
OL,18,Fsooner based on the results.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1781273476
OL,3,CDisgraced surgeon's patient 'failed at
OL,4,Cevery stage' by entire system
OL,6,FThe court also heard evidence Tracey
OL,7,Fwasn't initially given radiotherapy
OL,8,Ffor her breast cancer and that her
OL,9,Fchemotherapy treatment was stopped
OL,10,Fbefore the end of the cycle. Questions
OL,11,Fwere raised about why this was the
OL,12,Fcase.
OL,14,FPaterson did take out the lump, which
OL,15,Fwas still thought to be benign, in
OL,16,FMarch 1998, and further treatment was
OL,17,Fgiven over the coming months.
OL,19,FHowever, Tracey's cancer metastasised
OL,20,Fto her bones, and she had a recurrence
OL,21,Fof the cancer in her right breast.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1781273476
OL,3,CDisgraced surgeon's patient 'failed at
OL,4,Cevery stage' by entire system
OL,6,FDespite having a mastectomy and
OL,7,Fradiotherapy in 1999, she died at the
OL,8,Fend of the year,
OL,10,FPaterson gave evidence that his notes
OL,11,Fsay Tracey didn't want a mastectomy,
OL,12,Fsomething her family disputes.
OL,14,FHe also said he "worked hard" to give
OL,15,Fher a reconstruction at the same time
OL,16,Fas the mastectomy and says that, from
OL,17,Flooking at her notes, he believes the
OL,18,Fcancer had spread to her bones before
OL,19,Fshe had been seen by him.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1781273476
OL,3,CDisgraced surgeon's patient 'failed at
OL,4,Cevery stage' by entire system
OL,6,FTracey's family told ITV News Central:
OL,7,F"I do not entirely blame Ian Patterson
OL,8,Ffor everything.
OL,10,F"He had his failings, but so did the
OL,11,Fentire system. She was failed from the
OL,12,FGP right the way through to her first
OL,13,Fprocedures and right away certainly to
OL,14,Fprocedures by Ian Paterson."
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G7/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1781273476
OL,3,CDisgraced surgeon's patient 'failed at
OL,4,Cevery stage' by entire system
OL,6,FDescribing Tracey in a very moving
OL,7,F'pen portrait' in court, Norman Taylor
OL,8,Fsaid she was someone that people would
OL,9,Fgo to when they 'needed a situation
OL,10,Freading clearly' as she would give the
OL,11,Ftruth unequivocally but with 'warmth
OL,12,Fand with care.'
OL,14,FTracey was a graffiti artist in her
OL,15,Fyouth, entering competitions, before
OL,16,Fgoing to work in the jewellery trade,
OL,17,Fas a bridal model and then as a retail
OL,18,Fmanager.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G8/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1781273476
OL,3,CDisgraced surgeon's patient 'failed at
OL,4,Cevery stage' by entire system
OL,6,FShe and Norman met when she was 20,
OL,7,Fand whilst they had wanted children,
OL,8,Fher illness meant it wasn't possible.
OL,9,FNorman said her "life was short, but
OL,10,Fshe lived it fully."
OL,12,FThe outcome of Tracey's inquest is not
OL,13,Fdue until next year.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G9/9
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
